│ THOUGHT: Now I understand the issue! In the `simplifySelectWithEquivalence` │
│ function (lines 4628-4648), when we have an equality comparison like `icmp  │
│ eq ptr %a, %b`, it tries to substitute `%a` with `%b` in the true value and │
│ see if it simplifies to the false value.                                    │
│                                                                             │
│ In our case:                                                                │
│ - Condition: `icmp eq ptr %a, %b`                                           │
│ - TrueVal: `%a`                                                             │
│ - FalseVal: `%b`                                                            │
│                                                                             │
│ When it substitutes `%a` with `%b` in the true value (`%a`), it gets `%b`,  │
│ which equals the false value (`%b`). So it returns `FalseVal` (which is     │
│ `%b`).                                                                      │
│                                                                             │
│ However, this optimization is **not valid for pointers** in general because │
│ pointer equality doesn't guarantee that the pointers are interchangeable in │
│ all contexts. The Alive2 error shows a case where `%a` points to block 0    │
│ with offset -3, and `%b` points to block 1 with offset 0, but somehow the   │
│ comparison returns true (likely due to address aliasing in the memory       │
│ model). In this case, the select should return `%a` (the true value), not   │
│ `%b`.                                                                       │
│                                                                             │
│ The fix is to add a check that prevents this optimization when dealing with │
│ pointer types, or more specifically, when the values being compared are     │
│ pointers and the substitution might not be safe.                            │
│                                                                             │
│ Looking at the code, the issue is in the `simplifySelectWithEquivalence`    │
│ call within `simplifySelectWithICmpCond`. We need to add a condition to     │
│ skip this optimization for pointer types.                                   │
│                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                     │
│ sed -i '4733i\    // Don\'t perform equivalence substitution for pointer    │
│ types as it may not be safe\n    // due to potential differences in         │
│ provenance or memory layout.\n    if (CmpLHS->getType()->isPointerTy())\n   │
│ return nullptr;' ./llvm/lib/Analysis/InstructionSimplify.cpp                │
│ ```                                                                         │
